Note: ============================================================================
Note: Fast Name-to-Number Lookup
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "get_linux_arm32_syscall_number" that takes name as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Returns the syscall number for a given syscall name on Linux ARM32
    Note: Uses direct string comparison for fast lookup without requiring a registry
    Note: Returns -1 if the syscall name is not recognized

    Note: --- File I/O ---
    If StringCore.string_equals(name, "read") is equal to 1:
        Return SYS_ARM32_READ
    End If
    If StringCore.string_equals(name, "write") is equal to 1:
        Return SYS_ARM32_WRITE
    End If
    If StringCore.string_equals(name, "open") is equal to 1:
        Return SYS_ARM32_OPEN
    End If
    If StringCore.string_equals(name, "close") is equal to 1:
        Return SYS_ARM32_CLOSE
    End If
    If StringCore.string_equals(name, "lseek") is equal to 1:
        Return SYS_ARM32_LSEEK
